{"overview":"This B minor fugue exhibits a richly chromatic harmonic character rooted in diatonic circle-of-fifths motion, punctuated by a striking enharmonic modulation through C# minor and a modal mixture pivot into D major, tracing an expansive tonal journey before a compressed stretto drives the work to its five-voice cadential conclusion. Its most distinctive feature is the interplay between the sighing, chromatically saturated subject and the increasingly dense stretto entries, which generate mounting contrapuntal tension resolved only by the final plagally-tinged perfect authentic cadence in B minor.","cross_piece_tags":["fugue","counterpoint","chromatic_mediant","modal_mixture","enharmonic_modulation","circle_of_fifths","tragic","dramatic"]}
